cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with facial attribute extraction using deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) and the robustness of these networks to adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training of DCNNs, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of adversarial attacks and the study of their effects on the networks falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the concept of natural adversarial samples, which could be related to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with facial attributes, which could be related to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
